title: 2  Abstract
text: Write your abstract here. Your thesis abstract presents a concise summary of the thesis (research problem or issue, the methods or approach used, and results).

title: 3  Introduction
text: Write your introduction here. You should present the topic and relevant background information. Detail the research problem and hypothesis and provide an overview of the key points of the paper.

title: Duke Statistical Science Undergraduate Thesis Template
6  Results
text:
Write your results here. Report the findings of your study based upon the information gathered as a result of the methodologies you applied. It should simply state the findings, without bias or interpretation, and arranged in a logical sequence.

6.0.1 Cross Referencing Tables and Figures
Within your results and discussion, you can refer to specific figures and tables from your methodologies such as Figure 5.1.

title: 7  Conclusion
text: Write your conclusion here. Conclusions should summarize the problem, the solution and its main innovative features, outlining future work on the topic or application scenarios of the proposed solution.

title: 5  Methodology
text:
Write your methodology here. This discusses and explains the data collection and analysis methods you used in your research. Include any relevant graphs, tables, and visualizations.

title: 4  Literature Review
text: Write your literature review here. This provides an overview of current knowledge, allowing you to identify relevant theories, methods, and gaps in the existing research that you can apply to your thesis.

title: 8  Appendix
text: Write your appendix here. You can include any supplementary information to facilitate understanding of your research. It is useful for providing additional information or clarification in your research thesis without making the final product too long.

text: Add references here, following standard formatting for bibliographical entries.
